Key Material Information (Quarterly Report - June 2025)

Operational & Financial Highlights:

  • Strategic Development Agreement (SDA) signed with Clean Energy Fuels Australia (CEFA) for the Rafael Gas Project (100% Buru-owned):
  • CEFA to finance, build, and operate an LNG plant (300 tonnes/day) at Rafael 1 well site.
  • Limits Buru’s financial exposure to upstream gas production only.
  • Targeting Final Investment Decision (FID) by mid-2026, first cash flow from late 2027.

  • Projected gross unrisked NPV: A$400M; annual pre-tax cash flow: ~A$70M (based on A$15/GJ gas, A$1.50/litre condensate).

  • Divestment of non-core assets:

  • Sold 2H Resources Pty Ltd and certain Canning Basin blocks to Koloma Australia for up to A$2M (A$1M upfront, A$1M staged).

  • Retains option to buy back 30% interest in future hydrogen discoveries.

  • Ungani Oilfield:

  • Cash Position:

ASX Announcement Summary – MyEco Group Ltd (ASX: MCO) – Q4 FY25 Sales Update

Key Financial & Operational Highlights:

  • Total FY25 sales: $15.7m (up 8.6% YoY).
  • MyEco® Global Sales: $5.3m (up 81.8% YoY) – category leader in Coles (39% market share) and Woolworths (59% market share).
  • USA sales impacted by US tariff policy uncertainty (Q4 sales: $0.10m vs $0.25m in Q3).
  • White Label Sales: $2.7m (up 15.0% YoY) – boosted by new UK retail customer (Home Bargains).
  • Council/Waste Sales: $4.7m (down 2.1% YoY) – $0.9m Ballarat Council tender delayed to FY26, but growth expected due to FOGO program expansions.
  • Resin Sales: $2.3m (down 36.9% YoY) due to shift in production focus toward MyEco® products.
  • Film Sales: $0.66m (down 7.6% YoY) – minor segment but in trials for expanded applications.

Cost Savings & Outlook:

  • FY26 fixed cost savings: ~$2.5m from restructuring.
  • NSW FOGO mandate (by 2030) and food-waste separation requirements (from 2026) expected to support future council sales growth.
  • Sales strategy remains focused on positive EBITDA in the medium term.

Conclusion: Strong branded growth offset by resin decline and US volatility; cost optimization and policy tailwinds support FY26 outlook.

• Clinical Trial Update (Phase 1b azer-cel CAR T therapy)
  • 75% Overall Response Rate (ORR): 6 Complete Responses (CR) and 3 Partial Responses (PR) in relapsed DLBCL patients.
  • Durability: First patient remains cancer-free at 15+ months; others show durable responses at 2, 5, and 11+ months.
  • High-Unmet-Need Population: Patients had failed 3–6 prior therapies, including autologous CAR-T.
  • Regulatory Milestone: FDA Fast Track Designation secured; Type B (End of Phase 1) meeting planned for Q4 2025 to discuss pivotal trial design.
  • Trial Expansion: Now enrolling CAR T-naïve patients with other lymphomas (PCNSL, CLL/SLL, MZL, WM, FL).
